
@startuml

' Define classes and their relationships
class Location {
    - address: String
}

class Driver {
    - firstName: String
    - lastName: String
}

class Vehicle {
    - vehicleNumber: String
}

class Truck {
    - weight: Double
}

class Car {
    - numberOfSeats: Integer
}

class Van {
}

class Order {
    - originLocation: Location
    - destinationLocation: Location
    - executionDate: Date
}

' Inheritance for Vehicle types
Vehicle <|-- Truck
Vehicle <|-- Car
Vehicle <|-- Van

' Relationships
Driver "1" --> "0..1" Vehicle : drives
Driver "1" --> "1" Order : carries out
Order "1" --> "1" Driver : assigned to
Order "1" --> "1" Location : origin
Order "1" --> "1" Location : destination

@enduml

---

### Explanation of the Diagram:
- **`Location`**: Has an address.
- **`Driver`**: Has first and last name. Can drive at most one `Vehicle`, and can carry out one `Order` at a time.
- **`Vehicle`**: Base class with a `vehicleNumber`. Three subclasses: `Truck`, `Car`, and `Van`.
  - `Truck` has a `weight`.
  - `Car` has a `numberOfSeats`.
  - `Van` has no additional attributes.
- **`Order`**: Contains origin and destination locations, execution date, and is carried out by exactly one driver.

